<H2><A NAME=research> Research Projects:</H2>

<MENU>
<DL>

<DT> <!WA35><IMG SRC="http://www.cs.uiowa.edu/~cremer/images/smallIsaacLogo.gif"> <!WA36><A HREF="http://www.cs.uiowa.edu/~isaac">Isaac: Simulation for Virtual Environments</A>. <br> <br>


<DT> <!WA37><a href="http://www.cs.uiowa.edu/~hank"> HANK </a>: small CS dept. driving simulator for use in scenario and scene
authoring research.  Work in cooperation with Ford Motor Co. <br> <br>

<DT> Behavior Simulation and
	Control - <!WA38><a href="http://www.cs.uiowa.edu/~kearney/scenario.html">The
	  Scenario Home Page </a> </li> <br><br>

<DT> <!WA39><IMG SRC="http://www.cs.uiowa.edu/~cremer/images/bay-icon.gif"> Iowa Driving Simulator: scenario control and
experiment authoring for real-time operator-in-the-loop virtual environments.
Work in cooperation with Iowa's <!WA40><A href="http://www.ccad.uiowa.edu"> Center for Computer Aided Design</A>.<br><br>

<DT> <!WA41><IMG SRC="http://www.cs.uiowa.edu/~cremer/images/simlab-small.gif"> programming environments for development of physical systems simulators.  Originally had close ties to larger-scope SimLab project
at Cornell University: <!WA42><A HREF="http://www.cs.cornell.edu/Info/Projects/SimLab/"> SimLab project at Cornell</A>.


</DL>
</MENU>


